<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="210">3.3. Linking an existing contact to an account</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you have created the contact without linking them to an account, you can link the account afterwards as well. In order to avoid confusion with accounts having the same name, the town, street and country of the account are also displayed next to the account name.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Enter at least 3 characters of the account name, town, street or country. Your plentymarkets system suggests account data records that have already been saved.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Linking an existing contact to an account:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CRM » Contacts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Search (<span class="icon blue"><i class="fa fa-search  "></i></span>) the contact by means of the filter settings as described in the <a href="/en/crm/managing-contacts#200">Searching for a contact</a> chapter.<br>
→ The contacts that correspond to the search criteria entered are displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click in the line of the contact.<br>
→ The detail view of the contact opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the name of the account, town, street or country in the input field of the <strong>Account</strong> area.<br>
→ Once you have entered 3 characters, account data records that have already been saved are suggested.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the account data record from the drop-down list.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.<br>
→ All account-related data is displayed in the detail view of the contact.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="220">3.4. Creating an account</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Create the account and save data such as the VAT number, payment due date and percentage for early payment discount.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Creating an account:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CRM » Contacts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Search (<span class="icon blue"><i class="fa fa-search  "></i></span>) the contact by means of the filter settings as described in the <a href="/en/crm/managing-contacts#200">Searching for a contact</a> chapter.<br>
→ The contacts that correspond to the search criteria entered are displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click in the line of the contact.<br>
→ The detail view of the contact opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the <strong>Account</strong> area, click on <strong>Add new account</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-plus-square  "></i></span>).<br>
<span class="icon "><i class="fa fa-map-signs  "></i></span> <strong><em>Or:</em></strong> Enter the name of the account in the suggestion list and click on <strong>Save</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the desired settings. Note <a href="#table-edit-contact">Table 6</a> in the <strong>Account</strong> area.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.<br>
→ The account is created and the detail view of the contact opens.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Loading already existing account data records</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Account data records that have been already saved are only loaded when clicking in the suggestion field once you have entered at least 3 letters of the account name.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="230">3.5. Editing the account</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you have edit account data that is already saved, the data of the existing account data record is overwritten.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Editing the account:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CRM » Contacts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Search (<span class="icon blue"><i class="fa fa-search  "></i></span>) the contact by means of the filter settings as described in the <a href="/en/crm/managing-contacts#200">Searching for a contact</a> chapter.<br>
→ The contacts that correspond to the search criteria entered are displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click in the line of the contact.<br>
→ The detail view of the contact opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the <strong>Account</strong> area, click on <strong>Edit</strong> (<span class="icon yellow"><i class="fa fa-pencil  "></i></span>).</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the desired changes. Note <a href="#table-edit-contact">Table 6</a> in the <strong>Account</strong> area.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.<br>
→ The data of the edited account is overwritten and the data of the newly created account displayed in the detail view of the contact.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="240">3.6. Deleting the link between account and contact</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can delete the link between the account and the contact in the detail view of the contact. Note that you only delete the link and not the account data itself. The account data is still displayed as a suggestion in the drop-down list after you have entered at least 3 characters of the account name, town, street or country.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Deleting the link between account and contact:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CRM » Contacts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Search (<span class="icon blue"><i class="fa fa-search  "></i></span>) the contact by means of the filter settings as described in the <a href="/en/crm/managing-contacts#200">Searching for a contact</a> chapter.<br>
→ The contacts that correspond to the search criteria entered are displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click in the line of the contact.<br>
→ The detail view of the contact opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click in the entry field in the <strong>Account</strong> area.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the empty option.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.<br>
→ The link between the account and the contact is deleted.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="300">3.7. Editing a contact</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Search the contact by means of the <a href="/en/crm/managing-contacts#200">filter settings</a>. Open the contact by clicking in the line of the contact to edit the contact’s data such as the date of birth, telephone number and email address, for example, or to add further information. Click on <strong>Delete contact option</strong> (<span class="icon red"><i class="fa fa-minus-square  "></i></span>) to delete the contact option.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Editing a contact:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CRM » Contacts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
